use v5.34;
use utf8;
use open qw(:std :utf8);

use FindBin qw($Bin);
use lib "$Bin/../lib";

use Mojo::Util qw(dumper);
use Term::ANSIColor;
use Local::CPANSA qw(:cve);

=encoding utf8

=head1 NAME

list_cves - show all the CVEs that mention "perl"

=head1 SYNOPSIS

Run this from the top level of the repository:

	% perl util/list_cves
	...
	✔  CVE-2026-41564    CryptX versions before 0.088 for Perl do not reseed the Crypt::PK PRNG s
	*  CVE-2026-44128    SEPPmail Secure Email Gateway before version 15.0.2.1 allows unauthentic
	?  CVE-2026-45179    Plack::Middleware::Statsd versions before 0.9.0 for Perl may leak user I

	Summary
	-------
	*: 162
	✔: 280
	?: 5

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This is just a quick command-line app to see what the reports for Perl are. A
check () in the first column means we already have recorded the report. An asterisk
(C<*>) means that we have evaluated the report and are ignoring it. A question
mark (C<?)> means that we have not yet evaluated that report.

You need to run this from the top level of the repository since it depends on
modules that are not distributed and not installed (in F<lib/Local>).

